techmeme.title: Job postings: Amazon has a new ZeroOne team focused on inventing "breakthrough" consumer products, and led by former Microsoft executive J Allard (Annie Palmer/CNBC)
Grammarly raised $1B in non-dilutive funding from General Catalyst to expand its AI tools; 2005-founded Grammarly has $700M+ in annual revenue and is profitable (Krystal Hu/Reuters)
Meta and Palmer Luckey's Anduril Industries partner to build EagleEye, a new AI-powered weapons system, including rugged helmets, glasses, and other wearables (Heather Somerville/Wall Street Journal)
Filing: virtual chronic care company Omada Health plans to raise up to $158M in its IPO, selling shares for $18 to $20 and aiming for an up to ~$1.1B market cap (Ashley Capoot/CNBC)
An Apple-funded study says the US App Store drove $406B in 2024 billings and sales, up from $142B in 2019, with developers paying no commission on 90% of sales (Andrew Orr/AppleInsider)
